partners with focused attention to the pressing needs of underserved individuals and populations.  A limited amount of funding is available to support UI Health faculty and staff who:   Provide educational learning experiences that promote competence in interprofessional collaborative practice across the seven health science colleges at UIC.  Implement or enhance interprofessional collaborative practice to achieve improvements in health professions education and health care delivery at UI Health.  Develop initiatives that can be shared and replicated by others at UI Health and the community.  Engage UI Health student and staff populations about IPE founded on principles of adult learning, team science, patient centered care and population health.  Embed interprofessional practices at the University of Illinois Hospital and federally qualified health centers.   Attachments for the application include:  Application Instructions  Budget template      IPE Funding Application    Applicant Information Principal Applicant College/Department Phone Number Email Project Information Project Title * Required Total Budget Requested: * Required Project Duration * Required 18 months maximum Proposal Narrative A.	Project and Methodology * Required Please describe the proposed project, the problem that will be addressed, and the methods and activities for which support is requested (500 words maximum). C.	Team Members * Required Please list all team members, respective roles, and qualifications (500 words maximum). D.	Evaluation * Required Please describe how the outcomes will be measured and indicate the measurement tools (500 words maximum). E. Project Timeline and Milestones * Required Please outline milestones for the duration of the proposed project (250 words maximum). F. Budget Summary * Required Personnel (salary and fringe benefits) Other Direct Costs (office operations, travel, etc.) Purchased Services (consultant or contract costs) Indirect costs (related administrative e